			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The ContextFlags field of the CONTEXT struct is supposed to be filled out before calling GetThreadContext() (see http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms679362(v=vs.85).aspx).  The call in service_runtime/win/thread_suspension.c does not do this.

This might mean that the GetThreadContext() call does not have the desired effect of waiting for the thread to suspend, if ContextFlags==0.  (This doesn't seem to be the case, though.)

Or it might mean we copy some context unnecessarily, slowing things down.
